Sodiq Oyeleke There was an explosion in Damaturu, Yobe State, on Monday after a military armoured tank caught fire. It was learnt that the explosion caused panic in the area. It was gathered that firefighters were immediately deployed to the scene to put off the fire. The incident reportedly occurred opposite the Federal Polytechnic Damaturu. Military’s spokesperson in the area, Njoka Irabor, confirmed the incident to our correspondent on the telephone. He couldn’t ascertain the level of casualty, but said “the situation is under control.” “As of now, I have not been able to ascertain the level of casualty. But it was just an unfortunate incident,” he added.